Package ohos.hiviewdfx

Class HiAppEvent

  • java.lang.Object
    • ohos.hiviewdfx.HiAppEvent

  • public class HiAppEvent
extends Object
    Provides the event logging function for applications to log the fault, statistical, security, and user behavior events reported during running. Based on event information, you will be able to analyze the running status of applications.

    You need to customize event names, parameters, and types based on your own requirements.

    The following is an example of the event logging code: 

     HiAppEvent.write("app_exception", HiAppEvent.EventType.FAULT, "num", 101, "reason", "connect fail");
    Since:
    6

    • Method Detail

      • write

        public static int write​(String eventName,
                        HiAppEvent.EventType type,
                        Object... keyValues)
        Implements asynchronous logging of application events whose parameters are of a variable length. Before logging an application event, this API will first verify parameters of this event. If the verification is successful, the API will write the event to the event file asynchronously.
        Parameters:
        eventName - Indicates the event name. You can customize the event name as needed.
        type - Indicates the event type, which is defined in EventType.
        keyValues - Indicates an array of event parameters, each of which is comprised of the parameter name and parameter value. The parameter name must be a string, and the parameter value must be a basic data element, a string, or a list (which can only be a basic data element or a string).
        Returns:
        Returns 0 if the event parameter verification is successful, and the event will be written to the event file asynchronously; returns a positive integer if invalid parameters are present in the event, and the event will be written to the event file asynchronously after the invalid parameters are ignored; returns a negative integer if the event parameter verification fails, and the event will not be written to the event file asynchronously.
        Since:
        6

      • write

        public static int write​(String eventName,
                        HiAppEvent.EventType type,
                        Map<String,Object> keyValues)
        Implements asynchronous logging of application events whose parameters are of the Map type. Before logging an application event, this API will first verify parameters of this event. If the verification is successful, the API will write the event to the event file asynchronously.
        Parameters:
        eventName - Indicates the event name. You can customize the event name as needed.
        type - Indicates the event type, which is defined in EventType.
        keyValues - Indicates an array of event parameters, each of which is comprised of the parameter name and parameter value. The parameter name must be a map key, and the parameter value must be a basic data element, a string, or a list (which can only be a basic data element or a string).
        Returns:
        Returns 0 if the event parameter verification is successful, and the event will be written to the event file asynchronously; returns a positive integer if invalid parameters are present in the event, and the event will be written to the event file asynchronously after the invalid parameters are ignored; returns a negative integer if the event parameter verification fails, and the event will not be written to the event file asynchronously.
        Since:
        6
